{"blocks":[{"key":"v709","text":"Pour room temperature media into plates in a biosafety cabinet - keep everything sterile! Allow media to cool and solidify, then package and store at 4 °C. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"16vk7","text":"Collect small aliquots of desired Arabidopsis seeds into clean microfuge tubes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9g382","text":"Add 500 uL of a solution made of 40% (v/v) household bleach, and 0.01% (v/v) Tween20 dissolved in distilled water and incubate for 5 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d5sji","text":"Remove supernatant, then rinse seeds with 700 uL of 70% ethanol incubating for 5-10 minutes. If you did not perform bleach sterilization step, repeat ethanol wash an additional 1-2 times.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bkknm","text":"Remove supernatant then rinse with distilled water at least 3 times.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9jvsm","text":"After final rinse, plate seeds out on media plates in sterile environment (e.g. BioSafety cabinet). Seeds can be stored at 4 °C for up to 1 month (maximum). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
